    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-03-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-03-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="239" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d239">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Smythe</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-03-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 16, 1895</hi>
                        </date>.
                                (Received March 26.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 21.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I am unofficially informed by Mr. Pichon,
                            the French minister here, and also by Dr. Llenas, the Dominican
                            minister, that the various matters in dispute between the French
                            Government and President Heureaux have been satisfactorily adjusted. Mr.
                            Pichon will soon go to Santo Domingo City to restore relations.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Henry M. Smythe</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
